	<h2>Mission</h2>
	<p>Code for Philly is an open group of citizens dedicated to reaping the potential benefits of web technology for Philadelphia.</p>
	<p>We were founded under <a href="http://codeforamerica.org">Code for America</a>'s inagural <a href="http://brigade.codeforamerica.org">brigade program</a> near the end of 2012</p>
	<p>According to Wikipedia, Code for America is "a non-partisan, non-political 501(c)3 organization founded in 2009 to bring web-industry professionals to work with city governments in the United States in order to promote openness, participation, and efficiency in municipal governments"</p>
